h 20 g of the peanut oil (approx. 1 tbsp). Drain shiitake mushrooms using simmering basket, then remove stems and discard. Slice mushroom cups, then transfer into a separate bowl to the noodles and set aside."},{"content":"Place garlic, spring onions\/shallots, chillies, coriander roots and stems and remaining 40 g peanut oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down side of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <b>2 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add prawns and sauté <b>1-2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>. Using a pair of tongs, carefully remove prawns from mixing bowl and transfer into the large serving bowl with the noodles. Leave remainder of contents in mixing bowl."},{"content":"Add calamari and sauté <b>1-2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>. Using a pair of tongs, remove calamari from mixing bowl and transfer into the large serving bowl with the prawns and noodles. Leave remainder of contents in mixing bowl."},{"content":"Add reserved shiitake mushroom slices, bamboo shoots, carrot, lime juice, fish sauce and palm sugar and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer all mixing bowl contents into the large serving bowl with the noodles, prawns and calamari."},{"content":"Place serving bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh sweet chilli sauce into it. Add tomatoes, reserved coriander leaves and reserved spring onion\/shallot fronds to serving bowl and gently combine with spatula."},{"content":"Season salad to taste with salt and pepper, then place into refrigerator to chill (approx. 30 minutes). Serve salad chilled, with extra finely sliced bird's eye chilli and lime wedges on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Clean the roots of your coriander before adding to the mixing bowl. Scrape down the root to remove the tougher, more fibrous bits on the outside."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","6 portions"]}